review_text: I took my wife for a walk there because she has been dying to see the Tulip Garden there,,, which was beautiful by the way. There must have been at least 1000 tulips,,, if not more. Peace out and Pay it Forward everyone.

Great place to lie in the grass, draw on a bench, or be reminded of Montreal's past.

Looks incredible when the fall leaves come. Nice place to watch the marmots play in the dandelions :)
It was very nice I need was a warm day
Definitely dog-friendly: in half an hour on the bench we saw a husky, a rottweiler, boxer, dachshund, even a coonhound
J'adore ce parc. Le bruit de l'industrie à côté est un peu énervant mais les arbres sont magestueux et il y a toujours peu de gens et beaucoup d'espace.

(Translated by Google) Very quiet and have enjoyed with the family

(Original)
Très tranquille et ont profite avec la famille

(Translated by Google) I really like the marguerite beaugeois park for the cleanliness and the tree maniacs and the tranquility

(Original)
J'aime beaucoup  le parc marguerite  beaugeois pour la propreté  et les maniaques arbre  et la tranquillité

(Translated by Google) Very nice place and good service

(Original)
Très belle endroit et bon service

(Translated by Google) Nice little park in a quiet neighborhood.

(Original)
Beau petit parc de quartier tranquille.

(Translated by Google) Fairly large park embellished by old tall elegant trees. Couples in their sixties hand in hand watching people go by, young mothers jogging with their strollers and dogs on a leash with their civilized masters. Perfect picnic sometimes with Terminator;)

(Original)
Parc assez vaste embellit par de vieux grands arbres élégants. Couples sexagénaires main dans la main regardant passer les gens, jogging de jeunes mères avec leurs poussettes et chiens en laisse avec leurs maîtres civilisés. Picnic parfait tantôt avec Terminator ;)
